The paper discusses decoding strategies for interference channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of rate-splitting and successive decoding is a coding technique that is commonly used in wireless communication systems, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
